Rule.Name: sOutlook15MsiPlusSfbC2R
Rule.Title: Outlook crashes and errors with Lync/Skype for Business
Rule.Text:
You have an 'MSI' installation of Outlook 2013 but your Skype for Business (formerly Lync) installation is 'Click-to-run'. This is an unsupported configuration and you can expect to see either crashes in Outlook or errors related to Outlook in Skype for Business.
Click the 'Click here ...' link for details on how to fix this issue.
Rule.Symptoms: Crash,Configuration (unsupported or problematic),Skype for Business integration

Object.Name: Outlook.exe not found in this path

Rule.Name: sLyncSfbNotDefaultIMProvider
Rule.Title: Non-Microsoft Instant Messaging client '{0}' is configured as the default IM provider
Rule.Text:
The '{0}' client is configured as the default Instant Messaging provider. This is not necessarily a problem configuration. But, if you are using a Microsoft IM client (Skype, Lync, or Communicator) as your IM client you may need to modify the DefaultIMApp value under 'HKCU\Software\IM Providers' in the registry.
Click the 'Tell me more ...' link for details.

Rule.Name: sSavePasswordNoSept2015Update
Rule.P1: if($nInstallType='MSI','and then install the update from the Microsoft Download site','and then update Office using the steps in the "Get the latest version of Office" section of the article')
Rule.Title: The SavePassword registry value is not being used (as expected) by Skype for Business
Rule.Text:
The SavePassword value was found in the registry under HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Office\{2}.0\Lync but it is not being used by Skype for Business because you do not have the update from September 8, 2015 (or a later update) installed.
After installing the September 8, 2015 update (or later update), you will also want to add the AllowSavePassword registry value. Please click the 'Click here ...' link for complete details.
To install the latest update for Skype for Business, click the 'Download the update ...' link {1}.

Rule.Name: sTurnOffPhotographLync
Rule.Title: Photographs for contacts are not displayed
Rule.Text:
Your contacts do not have their photographs displayed because the 'Show user photographs when available' option (in Outlook) is disabled. It is disabled because TurnOffPhotograph=1 {0} under '{1}'.
Click the 'Click here ...' link for steps to re-enable this option.

Rule.Name: sMissing001e6603PropSkypeIssue
Rule.Title: Possible problems with the MAPI connection to Exchange Server
Rule.Text:
The MAPI connection to Exchange Server may not be available to Skype for Business 2016 clients due to missing information in the Windows Registry. When this issue occurs, the Skype for Business Configuration Information feature shows 'MAPI Unavailable.' Additionally, if you click the 'Conversations' tab and then click 'View more in Outlook,' you receive an error message that states 'Your Outlook profile is not configured correctly...' Delegate functionality may also be broken.
Click the 'Click here ...' link to see the solution to this problem.

Rule.Name: sDisableHttpConnectHKCU
Rule.Title: Possible connection problems because DisableHttpConnect=1 under HKCU\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Office\{2}.0\Lync
Rule.Text:
When DisableHttpConnect=1, Lync/Skype does not try to connect to the server by using HTTP if TLS or TCP are unavailable. By default, Lync/Skpe first attempts to connect to the server by using TLS or TCP and, if neither of these transport methods is successful, Lync/Skype tries to connect by using HTTP.
This is a non-default configuration. Click the 'Click here ...' link for details on this setting.
